This project implements deep learning models for defect classification on the NEU-DET dataset from Kaggle using TensorFlow.
Dataset: The NEU-DET dataset contains grayscale images of six different types of surface defects found in steel strips.
Classes:Crazing, Inclusion, Patches, Pitted Surface, Rolled-in Scale, Scratches

Source: Kaggle â€“ NEU Surface Defect Detection Dataset
The experiments compare:
Data augmentation vs. no augmentation

Custom CNN vs. transfer learning using VGG16 (no augmentation)

Model architectures:
Custom CNN
VGG16-based transfer learning model

Optimizers:
Adam
SGD
